Overall Performance Tab for Numeric Use Cases

The Overall Performance tab shows metrics for key indicators and model quality.

Navigate to the Overall Performance Tab

In Performance, click Model Evaluation, then Overall Performance.

Summary Metrics
R2 measures the model's ability to explain variation in the outcome.
MAE Mean Absolute Error. Measures the absolute difference between the actual value and the prediction.
RMSE Root Mean Squared Error. Represents the square root of MSE (Mean Squared Error).

Predicted vs Actual

Use this scatter plot to visually compare the model's predicted outcomes with actual outcomes.

Residuals

Use this scatter plot to see the difference between the actual and predicted values (residuals), by predicted value.

Choose the type of residuals you want to see. Residuals shows the difference between the actual and predicted values, or the raw residual values. Standardized Residuals shows raw residual values divided by the standard deviation.

TIP Standardized residuals are useful for identifying outliers.

Normal QQ Plot for Standardized Residuals

For regression models, one of the key assumptions is that the residual errors for the outcome variable are normally distributed.
